AN ACT making an appropriation to the Office of Finance in the Office of the
Governor for a loan to the Office of the Chief Information Officer
within the Office of the Governor for the replacement of
uninterruptible power supply equipment and related expenses; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. There is hereby appropriated from the State General Fund to
2 the Office of Finance in the Office of the Governor for a loan to the Office of the
3 Chief Information Officer within the Office of the Governor for the
4 replacement of uninterruptible power supply equipment and related licensing and
5 maintenance expenses the following sums:
6 For the Fiscal Year 2025-2026 ........................................................ $790,902
7 For the Fiscal Year 2026-2027 ............................................................ $9,450
8 2. The amounts appropriated by subsection 1 are a loan. Commencing on
9 July 1, 2027, the Chief Information Officer shall use revenues from
10 intergovernmental transfers to repay the loan in annual installments to the
11 State Treasurer for deposit in the State General Fund. Each annual
12 installment must be 25 percent of the loan, and the loan must be fully repaid
13 not later than the end of Fiscal Year 2030-2031.
14 3. Any balance of the sums appropriated by subsection 1 remaining at the end
15 of the respective fiscal years must not be committed for expenditure after June 30

